Minnesota-Duluth Will Play Michigan in Final of NCAA Men’s Ice Hockey

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-08T04:01:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/minnesota-duluth-will-play-michigan-in-final-of-ncaa-men-s-ice-hockey.html
The University of Minnesota-Duluth
will play the  University of Michigan  in men’s college ice
hockey’s national final.  Minnesota-Duluth defeated Notre Dame 4-3 and  Michigan  beat
North Dakota 2-0 last night to reach the National Collegiate
Athletic Association title game tomorrow at Xcel Energy Center
in St. Paul, Minnesota.  Minnesota-Duluth is seeking its first national title, while
Michigan is looking for its 10th championship since 1948.  Jack Connolly, J.T. Brown, Mike Connolly and Kyle Schmidt
scored for Duluth (25-10-6), which defeated top-seeded Yale to
reach the semifinal. T.J. Tynan, Jeff Costello and Calle
Ridderwall had goals for the Fighting Irish (25-14-5).  For Michigan (29-10-4), Ben Winnett scored in the first
period and Scooter Vaughan added a goal with 35.8 seconds left
in the game. Shawn Hunwick made 40 saves for his fourth shutout
of the season.  The Wolverines snapped  North Dakota ’s (32-9-3) 15-game
unbeaten streak.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  